Common Dishwasher Issues We Repair
Dishwasher Not Draining Properly

Indicators: Standing water at the bottom after the cycle, foul odors, or mid-cycle error codes.
Possible Causes: A clogged filter, blocked drain hose, or malfunctioning pump.
Helpful Resource: Learn how to deal with a clogged filter from posts like “How to Clean a Kenmore Dishwasher Filter” or tackle draining issues in “Why Your Dishwasher Won’t Drain”.

Leaking Dishwasher

Indicators: Water pooling around your unit, damp cabinets or floors, or visible drips under the door.
Possible Causes: Worn door seals, cracked hoses, or a compromised pump assembly.
Helpful Resource: See “An Easy Fix for a Leaking Dishwasher”.

Poor Cleaning Results

Indicators: Food particles left on dishes, cloudy glassware, or residue baked onto plates.
Possible Causes: Spray arm blockages, worn-out wash impellers, or incorrect detergent usage.
Helpful Resource: Learn more about boosting wash performance in “Why Won’t My Dishwasher Clean My Dishes?” or check out “Top Dishwasher Troubleshooting Tips”.

Dishwasher Won’t Start or Loses Power Mid-Cycle

Indicators: Unresponsive controls, abrupt cycle cancellations, or blinking LED lights.
Possible Causes: Faulty door latch switches, defective control boards, or loose connections.
Helpful Resource: Explore “Why Does My Dishwasher Suddenly Have No Power?” and “How to Fix Your Dishwasher When It Won’t Power Up”.

Strange Noises or Excessive Vibration

Indicators: Grinding, knocking, or loud humming, especially during the wash or drain phases.
Possible Causes: Foreign objects caught in the chopper blade, defective motor bearings, or worn pump gaskets.
Helpful Resource: Check “Simple Solutions for a Noisy Dishwasher”.

Longer Than Usual Cycles or Stopping Mid-Cycle

Indicators: Cycle times that exceed the norm by 30+ minutes, or a cycle that restarts unexpectedly.
Possible Causes: Faulty sensors, heating element issues, or programming glitches.
Helpful Resource: Browse “Why Is My Dishwasher Stopping Mid-Cycle?” or “Average Dishwasher Run Time and Troubleshooting Tips”.

DIY QUICK FIXES: DISHWASHER TROUBLESHOOTINGIf your dishwasher won't start...
Open the door and close it firmly to ensure it's closed properly.
Make sure that you are closing the door within 3 seconds of pressing start if it has a top-button control.
Confirm that it's recieving power. If lights on the display don't turn on when you press them, reset the breaker and try again.
Check that the Control Lock or Delay Start options aren't selected on the display--your dishwasher won't start as expected in these modes.
Make sure the water supply valve to your dishwasher is turned on all the way.
Clear any debris that may be caught under the float assembly located on the bottom of the dishwasher tub and be sure that it can move up and down freely.
If your dishwasher won't drain...
Ensure that the drain hose that connects to the garbage disposal and/or your sink's drain line is not kinked and that bends are not too sharp.
Check and clear any blockages in the drain hose.
If your dishwasher has an air gap (usually located on the countertop, parallel to the faucet), lift the cover off, unscrew the plastic cap, and clean any soil buildup with a paper clip.
If you've recently installed a new garbage disposal, confirm that the "knock out plug" was removed before the dishwasher drain hose was connected.
If your dishwasher is leaking...
Open the door and close it firmly to ensure it's closed properly.
Make sure the dishwasher is level side-to-side and front-to-back.
Adjust the rinse agent dispenser to a lower number setting to ensure that there is not too much rinse agent being dispensed.
Run the dishwasher without detergent to ensure the problem isn't caused by using too much detergent.
If the door won't stay closed...
Check for pots, pot handles, or other objects that may be extending out of the rack area.
Clear away any foreign objects or food debris that has built up on the door gasket (the soft rubber seal that runs around the door).
If your dishwasher is new, you may need to push more firmly than usual on the door until the new door gasket softens up.
Make sure the lower rack is not in backwards by confirming that any plastic spacers on the rack are facing the door.
Make sure the dishwasher is level side-to-side and front-to-back.
If your dishes aren't getting cleaned...
Make sure that there is rinse aid in the dispenser.
Clean the detergent dispenser to ensure it's opening and dispensing correctly.
Clear the debris that may be caught under the float assembly located on the bottom of the dishwasher tub and be sure that it can move up and down freely.
Run the dishwasher without detergent to ensure the problem isn't caused by the use of too much detergent leaving reside on the dishes.
If the dishwasher isn't filling with water...
Open the door and close it firmly to ensure it's closed properly.
Make sure the water supply valve to your dishwasher is turned on all the way.
Clear any debris that may be caught under the float assembly located on the bottom of the dishwasher tub and be sure that it can move up and down freely.
Check the display and confirm that your dishwasher is not running in Demo Mode.

full_content.content: Glossary TermsWhat is a Dishwasher Basket?A dishwasher basket is a removable container designed to securely hold small items like cutlery and utensils during the wash cycle, ensuring efficient cleaning without loss or damage.What is a Dishwasher End Panel?A dishwasher end panel is a finishing piece installed on the exposed side of a dishwasher, primarily when it is at the end of kitchen cabinetry, to ensure a seamless and aesthetically pleasing look in the kitchen.What is a Dishwasher Diverter Motor?A dishwasher diverter motor controls the direction of water flow to different spray arms within the dishwasher, ensuring optimal water distribution during each wash cycle for thorough cleaning.What is a Dishwasher Drawer?A dishwasher drawer is a compact, space-saving kitchen appliance designed to clean dishes efficiently, resembling a standard kitchen drawer that slides out for easy loading and unloading.
